Jazz Horns Gold blows its own trumpet [and saxophone and 
nose flute] with a cool array of BBC archive from the jazz 
vaults.
Legends such as Dizzy Gillespie, Coleman Hawkins, Stan Getz 
and Rahsaan Roland Kirk play boldly alongside new stars who 
emerged in the 80s like Wynton Marsalis and the young jazz 
disciples of the 21st century such as Joshua Redman and 
Hypnotic Brass Ensemble. Not forgetting the Brits including 
Acker Bilk, John Dankworth, Courtney Pine and John Surman 
and the late, lamented Andy Hamilton. Archive sources include 
Jazz 625, the Late Show, Later with Jools Holland and 
Crackerjack.Blow man blow!
